CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 8, 1965, pg. 1 reads: "Moore's Sister Faints - Two unidentified men who attended the funeral of sportsman Alfonzo Moore, on Friday, catch his sister, Mrs. Virginia Moore Pratt, as she faints in the doorway of St. Luke Baptist Church, prior to being escorted to a funeral car for the trip to the burial site. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Virginia Moore Pratt, fainting, being escorted by two unidentified men down steps of St. Luke Baptist Church after funeral service for brother Alfonzo Moore
